msgid ""
"Unfortunately each build-system defines its own mechanisms for setting "
"compiler and optimization methods. **You will need to work out the correct "
"approach to set the LLVM optimization flags for your system**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Building-Projects.rst:148
msgid "Some build systems have a flag like ``./configure --enable-optimize``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Building-Projects.rst:150
msgid ""
"JavaScript/WebAssembly optimizations are specified in the final step "
"(sometimes called \"link\", as that step typically also links together a "
"bunch of files that are all compiled together into one JavaScript/"
"WebAssembly output). For example, to compile with :ref:`-O1 <emcc-O1>`:"
